    {
      "id": "6164a18c-7789-4031-821b-24581c0a9290",
      "type": "description",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Pour $x \\in \\R$ on pose $f(x) = \\sum_{n=1}^\\infty x^n\\sin\\frac1{\\sqrt n}$.",
        "html": "<p>Pour <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x \\in \\R\\)</span> on pose <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f(x) = \\sum_{n=1}^\\infty x^n\\sin\\frac1{\\sqrt n}\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "257098bf-db17-4d78-9532-5bd06044974e",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Déterminer le rayon de convergence, $R$, de cette série.",
        "html": "<p>Déterminer le rayon de convergence, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(R\\)</span>, de cette série.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "70138a18-08e8-4ed3-874f-3131e32bf841",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$R=1$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(R=1\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "54d88fce-a6be-49d9-b637-5ab2e32694bc",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "\\'Etudier la convergence de $f$ pour $x = \\pm R$.",
        "html": "<p>Étudier la convergence de <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f\\)</span> pour <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x = \\pm R\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "392d24bf-f580-4be3-9fb0-117db1a14339",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$x=-1  \\Rightarrow $ cv (série alternée), $x=1  \\Rightarrow $ dv.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(x=-1  \\Rightarrow\\)</span> cv (série alternée), <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x=1  \\Rightarrow\\)</span> dv.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "6ef8fc54-a306-475f-a6ec-c212bd7a5b29",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Déterminer $\\lim_{x\\to R^-} f(x)$.",
        "html": "<p>Déterminer <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\lim_{x\\to R^-} f(x)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "500c43ec-2bae-4ba8-a97f-493e4088886d",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$f$ est croissante sur $[0,1[$ donc $L$ existe dans $[0,+\\infty]$.\n\n             $L = \\sup\\limits_{[0,1[} f(x)\n              \\ge \\sup\\limits_{[0,1[} \\sum_{n=1}^N x^n\\sin\\frac1{\\sqrt n}\n              \\ge \\sum_{n=1}^N \\sin\\frac1{\\sqrt n}  \\Rightarrow  L = +\\infty$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(f\\)</span> est croissante sur <span class=\"math inline\">\\([0,1[\\)</span> donc <span class=\"math inline\">\\(L\\)</span> existe dans <span class=\"math inline\">\\([0,+\\infty]\\)</span>.</p>\n<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(L = \\sup\\limits_{[0,1[} f(x)\n              \\ge \\sup\\limits_{[0,1[} \\sum_{n=1}^N x^n\\sin\\frac1{\\sqrt n}\n              \\ge \\sum_{n=1}^N \\sin\\frac1{\\sqrt n}  \\Rightarrow  L = +\\infty\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    }
  ]
